Here is a simple JavaScript code snippet that achieves this:

```javascript
for(let i = 0; i <= 127; i++) {
    console.log(`ASCII ${i}: \u${i.toString(16)}`);
}
```
This script uses the `\u{hexadecimal code}` syntax in JavaScript to display the Unicode (UTF-8) representation of each ASCII character from 0 to 127. 

The for loop iterates over each number from 0 to 127, and the console.log() statement prints out each ASCII character along with its corresponding hexadecimal code.
